description:
Responsibilities:

Lead the production line to optimize the production efficiency;
Responsible for formulating supply chain strategy and perform cost management or processing procurement orders
Review the production capacity regularly to ensure the product deliver on time;
Monitor the workflow of the production to ensure the operation run smoothly;
Continuously improve the product quality to reduce the food risk;
Communicate with the team and management to reach the common goal;
Formulate and implement the standard the operation procedure;
Work with internal parties i.e: sales team to coordinate delivery schedule or stock arrangement;
Perform ad hoc duties

Requirements:

Bachelor's degree in relevant disciplines
With at least 8 years experience in food and beverage manufacturing, not less than 5 years experience in factory management
Work experience in large-scale of food and beverage manufacturing is preferred
Equipping with HACCP / ISO quality management standards qualifications
Strong interpersonal skill and good leadership skills Result-oriented, detailed mined and organized
Proactive, detail-minded and willing to take up challenges
Proficient in PC application including Chinese word processing
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese / Cantonese
Less experience will be considered as Assistant Factory Manager;
Immediate available is preferable

Job Responsibilities

Take active roles in providing technical support and feasibility studies for new product launch;
Actively involved in line set up, layout planning and workers’ training plan;
Continue improvement on output and efficiency;
Monitor the day-to-day operations of the plant; 
Review and improve operational management for all levels in the plant to achieve effectiveness and efficiency;
Ensure a smooth plant operation that complies with internal policies and customer requirements;
Responsible for overseeing assembly and industrial engineering department;
Trouble shooting, problem solving, process improvement, automation, product testing, etc.;
Provide support to other departments in customers audit and enquiry;
Handle ad hoc assignments as require.

Job Requirements

University graduate in Production Management / Mechanical Engineering or Industrial engineering or related discipline;
A minimum of 10 years working experience of which at least 5 years in managing a sizeable PRC factory and managing people; experience in household electrical appliance is an advantage;
Fast pace, flexible mindset, willing to learn;
Excellent communication skills with fluency in spoken and written English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Strong problem solving, influencing skills, communication and people management skills;
Preferred to have knowledge and experience in LEAN manufacturing;
Strong knowledge in fixture and equipment;
Station in PRC Dongguan plant is required.

Interested parties, please send your full resume stating your expected salary and date of availability to the Human Resources Department for application.  We offer successful candidates an attractive remuneration packages (Basic salary + Bonus + Medical Scheme) and the opportunity to work in a dynamic and exciting environment.  (Data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only)

Job Description
Manage the daily operation and monitor the performance of production team and outsourced workers;
Responsible for manpower control and staff issue of production team;
Participate the planning and implementation of policy and procedures in the areas of product quality, manufacturing strategies, manpower and cost control;
Closely communicate with all shift and level of operation management to ensure the production is smooth and effective;
Coach and motivate the production team to accomplish production target and practice the group core values.Job Requirements
Bachelor or equivalent in Business Management, Manufacturing or related discipline;

5 years of working experience at supervisory level, preferably in labour-intensive industries;
Self-motivated, independent
A good team player with good communication skills;
Well-organized with good analytical skill;
Proficient in PC applications including Chinese word processing;
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese / Cantonese;
5-day work week;
Working location: Tai Po Industrial Estate (with shuttle bus);

Staff Benefits

Medical Insurance Coverage
Birthday & Wedding Leave
Free Meal & Shuttle Bus
Staff Purchase Benefits
All applications and data collected will be treated in strict confidence and used exclusively for recruitment purposes.  Only short listed candidates will be invited for interview.  The company will retain the applications for a maximum period of 6 months and may refer suitable candidates to other vacancies within the Group.

